":"1170年–歿","1170–Male":"1170年–歿","1199–Male":"1199年–歿","1145–Male":"1145年–歿","1145–Female":"1145年–歿","about 1170":"大約1170年","1145":"1145年","1199":"1199年","1170":"1170年","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"蘇格蘭哈丁頓史爾西頓","lifeSummary":"當Margaret Cumin於大約1170年出生在蘇格蘭哈丁頓史爾西頓時，她的父親William Cumming27歲，母親Hexilda27歲。她和Barton DeSeaton至少有1個兒子。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1170–":"大约1170年–殁","1170–Female":"1170年–殁","1170–Male":"1170年–殁","1199–Male":"1199年–殁","1145–Male":"1145年–殁","1145–Female":"1145年–殁","about 1170":"大约1170年","1145":"1145年","1199":"1199年","1170":"1170年","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"苏格兰哈丁頓史爾西頓","lifeSummary":"当Margaret Cumin于大约1170年出生在苏格兰哈丁頓史爾西頓时，她的父亲William Cumming27岁，母亲Hexilda27岁。她和Barton DeSeaton至少有1个儿子。"},"hr":{"about 1170–":"oko 1170.–preminula","1170–Female":"1170–preminula","1170–Male":"1170–preminuo","1199–Male":"1199.–preminuo","1145–Male":"1145–preminuo","1145–Female":"1145–preminula","about 1170":"oko 1170.","1145":"1145","1199":"1199.","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"cs":{"about 1170–":"okolo 1170–Zesnulá","1170–Female":"1170–Zesnulá","1170–Male":"1170–Zesnulý","1199–Male":"1199–Zesnulý","1145–Male":"1145–Zesnulý","1145–Female":"1145–Zesnulá","about 1170":"okolo 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"da":{"about 1170–":"omkring 1170–Afdød","1170–Female":"1170–Afdød","1170–Male":"1170–Afdød","1199–Male":"1199–Afdød","1145–Male":"1145–Afdød","1145–Female":"1145–Afdød","about 1170":"omkring 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Skotland"},"nl":{"about 1170–":"circa 1170–Overleden","1170–Female":"1170–Overleden","1170–Male":"1170–Overleden","1199–Male":"1199–Overleden","1145–Male":"1145–Overleden","1145–Female":"1145–Overleden","about 1170":"circa 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Schotland"},"en":{"about 1170–":"about 1170–Deceased","1170–Female":"1170–Deceased","1170–Male":"1170–Deceased","1199–Male":"1199–Deceased","1145–Male":"1145–Deceased","1145–Female":"1145–Deceased","about 1170":"about 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cumin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Muslim (mainly Somalia and Bangladesh, also Ghana): from a personal name based on Arabic <i>mu’min</i> ‘believer (in Islam), pious person’. <i>Al-Mu’min</i> ‘the Believer’ is an attribute of Allah (Koran 59:23). It is also the title of the 40th sura of the Koran. Compare   Momin   and   Memon  . — Note: Since Somalis traditionally do not have hereditary surnames, this name was in most cases registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US."],"variants":[{"name":"Momin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Karim, Akbar, Zulfiqar, Amirali, Sadruddin, Nasir, Salim, Sultan, Ahmed, Amir, Inayat, Nizar.","Muslim (Indian subcontinent): variant of   Mumin  ."]},{"name":"Memon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Abdul, Mohammed, Mohammad, Altaf, Haji, Iqbal, Ahmed, Ali, Ghulam, Haroon, Liaquat, Muhammad.","Pakistani and Indian (Gujarat): Muslim name, from an altered form of Arabic <i>muʿmin</i> ‘believer’ (see   Mumin  )."]},{"name":"Muminovic","meanings":["Bosniak (<b>Muminović</b>): patronymic from the Muslim personal name   Mumin  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Cumin was born about 1170, in Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, her father, William Cumming, was 27 and her mother, Hexilda, was 27. She had at least 1 son with Barton DeSeaton."},"et":{"about 1170–":"umbes 1170–Surnud","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1170–":"noin 1170–Kuollut","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1199–Male":"1199–Kuollut","1145–Male":"1145–Kuollut","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","about 1170":"noin 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1170–":"environ 1170–Décédée","1170–Female":"1170–Décédée","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1199–Male":"1199–Décédé","1145–Male":"1145–Décédé","1145–Female":"1145–Décédée","about 1170":"environ 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Margaret Cumin est née environ 1170, à Seton, Haddingtonshire, Écosse, son père, William Cumming, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Hexilda, avait 27 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Barton DeSeaton."},"de":{"about 1170–":"um 1170–Verstorben","1170–Female":"1170–Verstorben","1170–Male":"1170–Verstorben","1199–Male":"1199–Verstorben","1145–Male":"1145–Verstorben","1145–Female":"1145–Verstorben","about 1170":"um 1170","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1170":"1170","Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Als Margaret Cumin um 1170 in Seton, Haddingtonshire, Scotland geboren wurde, war ihr Vater William Cumming 27 und ihre Mutter Hexilda 27. Sie hatte mit Barton DeSeaton mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1170–":"about 1170–Desede","1170–Female":"1170–Desede","1170–Male":"1170–Desede","1199–Male":"1199–Desede","1145–Male":"1145–Desede","1145–Female":"1145–Desede","about 1170":"a